---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Me">
  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Me</h1>
      <div class="content">
        <p class="lead">
          I'm a developer passionate about building modern web applications 
          and learning cloud technologies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Currently exploring AWS services and infrastructure as code with OpenTofu. 
          This site is my first cloud project, where I'm learning about serverless 
          architecture, CI/CD pipelines, and modern web development.
        </p>
        <h2>What I'm Learning</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>AWS Cloud Services (Lambda, API Gateway, DynamoDB, CloudFront)</li>
          <li>Infrastructure as Code with OpenTofu</li>
          <li>Modern web frameworks (Astro, React)</li>
          <li>Serverless architecture patterns</li>
          <li>CI/CD with GitHub Actions</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>My Journey</h2>
        <p>
          I believe in learning by building. This portfolio site is a perfect example - 
          it's not just a showcase, it's a hands-on learning project that covers 
          everything from frontend development to cloud infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    padding: 4rem 1rem;
  }
  
  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: #111827;
  }
  
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #1f2937;
  }
  
  .content {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #374151;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  p {
    color: #4b5563;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    color: #374151;
  }
  
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    h1 {
      color: #f9fafb;
    }
    
    h2 {
      color: #e5e7eb;
    }
    
    .lead {
      color: #d1d5db;
    }
    
    p {
      color: #9ca3af;
    }
    
    ul {
      color: #d1d5db;
    }
  }
</style>
